<item>
 <title>Hurricane Sandy Potential Temperature</title>
 <link>https://www.vapor.ucar.edu/gallery/sandy-images/hurricane-sandy-potential-temperature</link>
 <description>&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-field-image-upload field-type-image field-label-hidden&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-item even&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://www.vapor.ucar.edu/sites/default/files/styles/100__wide/public/gallery/images/T1000m0150.jpg?itok=WC_xe_lN&quot; width=&quot;675&quot; height=&quot;547&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-item even&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Hurricane Sandy WRF-ARW 1000m potential temperature with horizontal wind vectors.  Key features include:  enhancement of Sandy&#039;s inner warm-core temperature when passing over the axis of the Gulf Stream; cyclonic encirclement of the cold continental polar air.  Both processes increased the baroclinicity and wind speeds surrounding Sandy&#039;s warm inner core and decreased the central pressure preceding landfall.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
