 <title>Hurricane Sandy Radar Reflectivity</title>
 <link>https://www.vapor.ucar.edu/gallery/sandy-images/hurricane-sandy-radar-reflectivity</link>
 <description>&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-field-image-upload field-type-image field-label-hidden&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-item even&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://www.vapor.ucar.edu/sites/default/files/styles/100__wide/public/gallery/images/dbz0150.jpg?itok=hmZySWGz&quot; width=&quot;675&quot; height=&quot;547&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-item even&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Hurricane Sandy WRF-ARW maximum radar reflectivity overlaid with 1000m horizontal wind vectors.  Key features:  Maintenance of convection near the central core, and widespread convective and stratiform precipitation along the encircling outer wind maximum on the west and southwest flanks of Sandy.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
