 <title>Hurricane Sandy Cloud-Top Temperature</title>
 <link>https://www.vapor.ucar.edu/gallery/sandy-images/hurricane-sandy-cloud-top-temperature</link>
 <description>&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-field-image-upload field-type-image field-label-hidden&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-item even&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://www.vapor.ucar.edu/sites/default/files/styles/100__wide/public/gallery/images/cttbarbsA0150.jpg?itok=lLTkbNfQ&quot; width=&quot;675&quot; height=&quot;547&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-item even&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Hurricane Sandy WRF-ARW cloud-top temperature overlayed with 1000m horizontal wind vectors.  Key features include: signature of dramatic anticyclonic outflow aloft on the western flank of Sandy and lower-tropospheric cyclonic cloud rotation and intermittent cold cloud top convective activity near inner core and outer cold air encirclement.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
