 <title>Potential vorticity at 1000 meters</title>
 <link>https://www.vapor.ucar.edu/gallery/hurricane-sandy/potential-vorticity-1000-meters</link>
 <description>&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-field-image-upload field-type-image field-label-hidden&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-item even&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://www.vapor.ucar.edu/sites/default/files/styles/100__wide/public/gallery/images/sandyAMSPV1000.jpg?itok=BjuZ9vGA&quot; width=&quot;675&quot; height=&quot;535&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-item even&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Top view of WRF-ARW 1000 meter potential vorticity (PV).  Key feature: encirclement of inner-core PV by the ourt PV filaments and subsequent radial contractionof the outer PV ring during intensification just before landfall.  Colored according to potential vorticity units (PVU).&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
