 <description>&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-field-image-upload field-type-image field-label-hidden&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-item even&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://www.vapor.ucar.edu/sites/default/files/styles/100__wide/public/gallery/images/sandyAMSPV322TTop.jpg?itok=k3A-kbPj&quot; width=&quot;675&quot; height=&quot;531&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-item even&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Top view of WRF-ARW potential vorticity (PV) on the 322-K isentropic surface. Key features include: encirclement of the Sandy inner-core diabatic PV tower by polar stratospheric potential vorticity after 12:00 UTC 29 October 2012; enhancement of extratropical cyclonic wave breaking by Sandy&#039;s anticyclonic outflow jet in its northwestern quadrant. Color indicates potential vorticity units (PVU). Discussed in &lt;a href=&quot;https://ams.confex.com/ams/93Annual/flvgateway.cgi/id/23249?recordingid=23249&quot;&gt;Mel Shapiro&#039;s presentation at the AMS 2013 Townhall&lt;/a&gt; &quot;A research-community perspective of the life cycle of Hurricane Sandy&quot;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
